Specific plan is that we could - in some way - cache the results of Navigation.getSiblings().
If the publication engine could manage some kind of cache, that it clears out at the start/end of each batch of (currently 50) pages, this would probably help in quite a big way.
Not sure how possible this might be.
Basically, RhinoInterpreter would need to expose a variable that we can test for, and a cache that we can use.
e.g.
var value;
if (Cache.enabled) {
  if (Cache.exists(key)) {
   value = Cache.get(key);
  } else {
    value = computeValue();
    Cache.set(key, value);
  }
} else {
    value = computeValue();
}
...you get the idea.
